    <section class="wp-section" data-lang="en">
      <h2>Chapter 2: The Problem</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>AI sessions often reset context, making long-term projects fragile.</li>
        <li>Humans are overwhelmed by daily tasks and lose track of higher-level goals.</li>
        <li>Multi-model, multi-tool setups tend to become unmaintainable.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        SCA acts as an â€œexternal prefrontal cortexâ€, providing a single place
        to manage context, goals and policies that all AI agents share.
      </p>
    </section>

