    <section class="wp-section" data-lang="en">
      <h2>Chapter 5: Temporal Memory &amp; Logs</h2>
      <p>
        Temporal Memory tracks <strong>how decisions emerged</strong> from sequences of context
        and interactions. It is stored as an event stream rather than raw chat transcripts.
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Key decisions are tagged as checkpoints.</li>
        <li>Memory is shared at the â€œperson OSâ€ level, not per product.</li>
        <li>Integrated with the self-diagnosis layer (v50).</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

