    <section class="wp-section" data-lang="en">
      <h2>Chapter 8: Safety &amp; Governance</h2>
      <p>
        SCA prioritizes <strong>explicit boundaries of automation</strong>
        rather than blind full autonomy.
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>High-risk actions always require explicit human approval.</li>
        <li>Decisions remain auditable via logs and checkpoints.</li>
        <li>Economic incentives are coupled with social value via v36.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

